\section{Empirical strategies}

This section presents the methodology to investigate the... The main identification strategy is the logistic regression model as following
$$y_{i}=\alpha_{0}+\alpha_{1}L_{i}+\alpha_{2}X'_{i}+\mu_{i}$$
in which $y_{i}$ is either job finding methods or labor market outcomes, $L_{i}$ is the dummies for pre-migration language skills (1: speak German well; 0: do not speak German at all), $X_{i}$ contains all control variables, $\mu_{i}$ is the idiosyncratic error term. 

